LAST CALL FOR PAPERS * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * FIRST INTERNATIONAL WORKSHOP on REVERSE ENGINEERING in INFORMATION SYSTEMS * * ( REIS'99 ) * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * To be held in conjunction with the 18 th conference on Conceptual Modeling ( ER'99 ) Paris ( France ) Nov . 15 - 18 , 1999 ( http : / / www . prism . uvsq . fr / er 99 ) SUBMISSION DEADLINE MAY 14 1999 * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * SCOPE : * * * * * * It is now widely acknowledged that the reverse and re-engineering activity is of crucial interest for software systems and databases . It has been recently highlighted by the year 2000 problem and , in Europe , by the lauching of the Euro currency . More generally , there is a need of models , methodologies and tools for providing a sound basis when updating old software or data systems . The aim of the workshop is to address the problems related to this activity . All dimensions of the reverse engineering process are explored : data or programs , conceptual / physical level of abstraction , application specific or general purpose approaches , organizational impact . . . TOPICS : * * * * * * * Topics relevant for submission include , but are not limited to : * Database reverse Engineering * Program understanding * Redocumentation * Semantics recovery * Migration strategies for legacy systems * Knowledge-directed Reverse Engineering Process * Emerging Reverse Engineering Technologies * Tools for Reverse Engineering * Reverse Engineering Projects and Case Studies * Relationship Between Database Reverse Engineering and Database Integration * Relationship Between Database Reverse Engineering and Data Mining * Cost model for reengineering and maintenance * Organizational aspects of CASSAM ( Computer Aided Software Support and Maintenance ) * Conceptual modeling in help desk systems , service center systems Programme Committee Chair * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * Jacques KOULOUMDJIAN , Institut National des Sciences Appliquees de Lyon - France ( Jacques . Kouloumdjian @ yy . yckqk . sp ) Programme Committee * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * Peter AIKEN , Virginia Commonwealth University- USA Jacky AKOKA , France CNAM- Isabelle COMYN-WATTIAU , ESSEC - France Roger Hsiang- Li CHIANG , Nanyang Technological University- Singapour Jean- Luc HAINAUT , Facultes Universitaires Notre Dame de la Paix - Belgium Paul JOHANNESSON , Stockholm University- Sweden Kathi Ogshead DAVIS , Northern Illinois University- USA Heinrich MAYR , Klagenfurt University - Austria Christophe RIGOTTI , Institut National des Sciences Appliquees de Lyon - France Michel SCHNEIDER , Universite de Clermont- Ferrand- France Peretz SHOVAL , Ben- Gurion University - Israel Zahir TARI , RMIT University - Australia PROCEEDINGS PUBLICATIONS * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * The workshop proceedings will be published by Springer in the Lecture Notes in Computer Science series . SUBMISSION DETAILS : * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * Authors are invited to submit original and previously unpublished papers ( in english ) no longer than 5000 words . Submissions should be sent by electronic mail in Postscript format to reis 99 @ vr . tbmwi . tjm . For more detailed information please refer to the workshop website : http : / / www . insa-lyon . fr / Labos / LISI / REIS 99
